 Despatch - Police in Despatch, Port Elizabeth, have appealed to the public to assist them in identifying the body of a man that was found in the bushes near Perseverance in Despatch on Monday. "At around 22:00, police were summoned to a scene of a decomposed body of a man. It is alleged that a cattle herder stumbled across the body while he was herding cattle," said police spokesperson, Sergeant Majola Nkohli. "It is also said that he thereafter walked to the police station to report the matter. "The deceased was wearing a grey top with greenish stripes and a blue overall pants with reflective stripes. "Police opened an inquest docket as no visible injuries could be identified." Police are urging anyone who has a missing person or may know of a missing person to contact the Despatch Detectives standby number at 082 441 7828 or Crime Stop on 08600 10111. Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. For great savings on life’s little pleasures visit Bargain Buys!  Know somebody who is getting married, Wedding and Function can assist.  Have kids, then you need to visit Kids Connection. Enjoy food and travel, then visit Home Food and Travel. Need assistance with an online presence, visit Agency One. 